                            <span class="current">NFC Payments</span>
                        </nav>
                        <!-- Page Title -->
                        <h1 class="page-title" id="mnfc_title">NFC Tap-to-Pay Payments</h1>
                        <p class="page-subtitle">Accept contactless payments instantly using NFC technology. Customers simply tap their phone or card on your device to complete a transaction — fast, secure, and convenient.</p>
                        <!-- NFC Hero Visual -->
                        <div class="nfc-hero-visual">
                            <div class="nfc-animation-container">
                                <div class="nfc-icon-center">
                                    <i class="fa fa-wifi"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="nfc-wave"></div>
                                <div class="nfc-wave"></div>
                                <div class="nfc-wave"></div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="nfc-hero-text">
                                <h3>Contactless Payment Made Simple</h3>
                                <p>MPay's NFC payment system lets you accept tap payments in under 2 seconds. No card readers needed — your smartphone is all you need.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Section: Setting Up NFC -->
                        <section class="doc-section" id="mnfc_content_setup">
                            <h2 id="setting-up-nfc">Setting Up NFC</h2>
                            <p>Before you can accept NFC payments, you need to enable NFC on your device and configure the MPay Merchant app to accept contactless payments.</p>
                            <h3 id="enable-nfc-device">Enable NFC on Your Device</h3>
                            <div class="callout info">
                                <div class="callout-icon">
                                    <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="callout-content">
                                    <strong>Prerequisite</strong>
                                    <p>Your device must have built-in NFC hardware. Check the <a href="#compatible-devices">Compatible Devices</a> section below to confirm your device is supported.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h4>Android Devices</h4>
                            <div class="steps">
                                <div class="step" data-step="1">
                                    <div class="step-title">Open Device Settings</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> on your Android device. You can find it in the app drawer or by swiping down on the notification shade.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="2">
                                    <div class="step-title">Find NFC Settings</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Connected Devices</strong> → <strong>Connection Preferences</strong> → <strong>NFC</strong>. On some devices, search for "NFC" in Settings.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="3">
                                    <div class="step-title">Enable NFC</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Toggle NFC to <strong>ON</strong>. Also enable <strong>Android Beam</strong> or <strong>Tap & Pay</strong> if available on your device.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="4">
                                    <div class="step-title">Verify NFC is Active</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">An NFC icon should appear in your status bar. You can also check by opening the MPay app — the NFC indicator will turn green.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h4>iOS Devices</h4>
                            <div class="steps">
                                <div class="step" data-step="1">
                                    <div class="step-title">Check iOS Version</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Ensure your iPhone is running <strong>iOS 14.0 or later</strong>. Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>General</strong> → <strong>About</strong> to verify.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="2">
                                    <div class="step-title">NFC is Always On</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">On iPhone 7 and later, NFC is enabled by default and cannot be manually toggled. Simply ensure MPay has permission to use NFC capabilities.</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="3">
                                    <div class="step-title">Grant NFC Permission</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">When first using NFC in the MPay app, you'll see a permission prompt. Tap <strong>Allow</strong> to enable NFC reader mode.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h3 id="configure-nfc-mpay">Configure NFC in MPay</h3>
                            <p>Once NFC is enabled on your device, configure the MPay Merchant app to accept NFC payments:</p>
                            <div class="steps">
                                <div class="step" data-step="1">
                                    <div class="step-title">Open MPay Merchant App</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Launch the MPay Merchant app and navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Payment Methods</strong>.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="2">
                                    <div class="step-title">Enable NFC Payments</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Toggle <strong>Accept NFC Payments</strong> to ON. The app will verify that your device supports NFC and it's properly configured.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="3">
                                    <div class="step-title">Set Default Amount (Optional)</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">You can set a default payment amount for quick NFC transactions. Go to <strong>NFC Settings</strong> → <strong>Default Amount</strong> and enter your preferred value.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="4">
                                    <div class="step-title">Test NFC Connection</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Tap the <strong>Test NFC</strong> button. The app will attempt to read any nearby NFC device. If successful, you'll see a green confirmation.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="code-block">
                                <div class="code-header">
                                    <span class="code-lang">Settings Path</span>
                                    <button class="code-copy-btn" aria-label="Copy to clipboard">
                                        <i class="fa fa-copy"></i> Copy
                                    </button>
                                </div>
                                <div class="code-body">
                                    <code>MPay Merchant App → Settings → Payment Methods → NFC Payments → Enable</code>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout success">
                                <div class="callout-icon">
                                    <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="callout-content">
                                    <strong>You're all set!</strong>
                                    <p>Once NFC is enabled and configured, you'll see a green NFC indicator on your dashboard. You're ready to accept contactless payments.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <hr class="section-divider">
                        <!-- Section: Accepting NFC Payments -->
                        <section class="doc-section" id="mnfc_content_accepting">
                            <h2 id="accepting-nfc-payments">Accepting NFC Payments</h2>
                            <p>Follow these steps to accept an NFC tap-to-pay transaction from a customer.</p>
                            <!-- NFC Flow Illustration -->
                            <div class="nfc-flow-illustration">
                                <div class="flow-step">
                                    <div class="flow-step-icon">
                                        <i class="fa fa-dollar-sign"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="flow-step-label">Enter Amount</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flow-arrow">
                                    <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flow-step">
                                    <div class="flow-step-icon">
                                        <i class="fa fa-wifi"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="flow-step-label">Tap to Pay</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flow-arrow">
                                    <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flow-step">
                                    <div class="flow-step-icon">
                                        <i class="fa fa-shield-alt"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="flow-step-label">Authenticate</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flow-arrow">
                                    <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flow-step">
                                    <div class="flow-step-icon">
                                        <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="flow-step-label">Confirmed</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h3 id="step-by-step-accepting">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>
                            <div class="steps">
                                <div class="step" data-step="1">
                                    <div class="step-title">Open the Payment Screen</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">From the MPay Merchant dashboard, tap the <strong>Accept Payment</strong> button or the <strong>"+" icon</strong> at the bottom of the screen.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="2">
                                    <div class="step-title">Select NFC as Payment Method</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Choose <strong>NFC / Tap to Pay</strong> from the payment method options. If NFC is your default, this may already be selected.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="3">
                                    <div class="step-title">Enter the Payment Amount</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Use the numeric keypad to enter the payment amount. You can also add an optional description or reference number for the transaction.</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="4">
                                    <div class="step-title">Tap "Ready to Accept"</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Tap the <strong>Ready to Accept</strong> button. Your device will enter NFC listening mode and display an animated NFC indicator showing it's ready.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="5">
                                    <div class="step-title">Customer Taps Their Device</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Ask the customer to tap their phone (with MPay Consumer app open) or NFC-enabled card on the back of your device. Hold devices together for 1-2 seconds.</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="step" data-step="6">
                                    <div class="step-title">Payment Confirmation</div>
                                    <div class="step-desc">Both devices will vibrate and show a success animation. A receipt is generated instantly and can be shared via SMS, email, or printed.</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout warning">
                                <div class="callout-icon">
                                    <i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="callout-content">
                                    <strong>Important Tip</strong>
                                    <p>Ensure there are no thick phone cases or metal objects between the two devices. NFC requires close proximity (within 4 cm) for a reliable connection.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h3 id="transaction-limits">Transaction Limits</h3>
                            <p>NFC payments have the following limits based on your merchant verification level:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Basic Verification:</strong> Up to <code class="inline">$500</code> per transaction, <code class="inline">$2,000</code> daily limit
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Standard Verification:</strong> Up to <code class="inline">$2,500</code> per transaction, <code class="inline">$10,000</code> daily limit
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Premium Verification:</strong> Up to <code class="inline">$10,000</code> per transaction, <code class="inline">$50,000</code> daily limit
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>To increase your limits, complete additional <a onclick="load_page('merchant_account_setup')" style="color:#2563eb;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:underline;">verification steps</a>.</p>
                        </section>
                        <hr class="section-divider">
                        <!-- Section: Compatible Devices -->
                        <section class="doc-section" id="mnfc_content_devices">
                            <h2 id="compatible-devices">Compatible Devices</h2>
                            <p>NFC payments require a device with NFC hardware. Below are the supported devices and their compatibility levels.</p>
                            <h3 id="device-requirements">Minimum Requirements</h3>
                            <div class="requirements-grid">
                                <div class="requirement-card">
                                    <div class="requirement-icon">
                                        <i class="fa fa-mobile-alt"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="requirement-info">
                                        <h4>NFC Hardware</h4>
                                        <p>Device must have built-in NFC chip. External NFC adapters are not supported.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card">
                                    <div class="requirement-icon">
                                        <i class="fa fa-microchip"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="requirement-info">
                                        <h4>Processor</h4>
                                        <p>ARM-based processor with Secure Element or Host Card Emulation (HCE) support.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card">
                                    <div class="requirement-icon">
                                        <i class="fab fa-android"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="requirement-info">
                                        <h4>Android 8.0+</h4>
                                        <p>Android Oreo (API 26) or later with Google Play Services enabled.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="requirement-card">
                                    <div class="requirement-icon">
                                        <i class="fab fa-apple"></i>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="requirement-info">
                                        <h4>iOS 14.0+</h4>
                                        <p>iPhone 7 or later running iOS 14 or newer for Core NFC framework support.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h3 id="device-list">Supported Device List</h3>
                            <div class="device-table-wrapper">
                                <table class="device-table">
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Device</th>
                                            <th>Platform</th>
                                            <th>NFC Type</th>
                                            <th>Status</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>iPhone 15 / 14 / 13 / 12 Series</td>
                                            <td>iOS 16+</td>
                                            <td>Core NFC</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge supported"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Fully Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>iPhone 11 / XS / XR / X</td>
                                            <td>iOS 14+</td>
                                            <td>Core NFC</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge supported"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Fully Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>iPhone 8 / 7</td>
                                            <td>iOS 14+</td>
                                            <td>Core NFC (Limited)</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge partial"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Partial</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Samsung Galaxy S24 / S23 / S22</td>
                                            <td>Android 12+</td>
                                            <td>HCE</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge supported"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Fully Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Samsung Galaxy A54 / A53 / A34</td>
                                            <td>Android 12+</td>
                                            <td>HCE</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge supported"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Fully Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Google Pixel 8 / 7 / 6</td>
                                            <td>Android 13+</td>
                                            <td>HCE</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge supported"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Fully Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>OnePlus 12 / 11 / 10</td>
                                            <td>Android 12+</td>
                                            <td>HCE</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge supported"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> Fully Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Xiaomi 14 / 13 / Redmi Note 12</td>
                                            <td>Android 11+</td>
                                            <td>HCE</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge partial"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Partial</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Devices without NFC hardware</td>
                                            <td>Any</td>
                                            <td>N/A</td>
                                            <td><span class="status-badge unsupported"><i class="fa fa-times-circle"></i> Not Supported</span></td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout info">
                                <div class="callout-icon">
                                    <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="callout-content">
                                    <strong>"Partial" Support Explained</strong>
                                    <p>Devices with partial support can read NFC tags and process payments but may have limitations with background NFC reading or slower response times. All core payment features work correctly.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <hr class="section-divider">
                        <!-- Section: NFC Troubleshooting -->
                        <section class="doc-section" id="mnfc_content_troubleshoot">
                            <h2 id="nfc-troubleshooting">NFC Troubleshooting</h2>
                            <p>If you're experiencing issues with NFC payments, review these common problems and solutions.</p>
                            <div class="trouble-item open">
                                <button class="trouble-header" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="trouble-1-body" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="trouble-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation"></i></span>
                                    <span>NFC not detected — "No NFC hardware found"</span>
                                    <span class="trouble-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="trouble-body" id="trouble-1-body">
                                    <p>This error means the app cannot find NFC hardware on your device. Try these steps:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Verify your device model is in the <a href="#compatible-devices">compatible devices list</a>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Connected Devices → NFC</strong> and ensure it's turned ON
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Restart your device and try again</li>
                                        <li>Check if any device management software is blocking NFC access</li>
                                        <li>If using a phone case, try removing it — some cases block NFC signals</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="trouble-item">
                                <button class="trouble-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="trouble-2-body" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="trouble-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation"></i></span>
                                    <span>Payment fails with "Connection timeout"</span>
                                    <span class="trouble-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="trouble-body" id="trouble-2-body">
                                    <p>A connection timeout means the NFC handshake took too long. Common causes:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Distance:</strong> Devices must be within 4 cm (about 1.5 inches) of each other
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Alignment:</strong> Align the NFC chips — usually located in the center-back of the phone
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Hold steady:</strong> Keep both devices still for at least 2 seconds during the tap
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Interference:</strong> Move away from other NFC-enabled devices or metal surfaces
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Network:</strong> Ensure you have a stable internet connection (Wi-Fi or cellular data)
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="trouble-item">
                                <button class="trouble-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="trouble-3-body" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="trouble-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation"></i></span>
                                    <span>Frequent disconnections during NFC payment</span>
                                    <span class="trouble-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="trouble-body" id="trouble-3-body">
                                    <p>If NFC connections drop frequently:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Ensure both devices have NFC enabled and are running the latest MPay app version</li>
                                        <li>Disable battery optimization for the MPay app: <strong>Settings → Battery → MPay → Don't optimize</strong>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Remove any thick or metallic phone cases</li>
                                        <li>Update your device firmware/OS to the latest version</li>
                                        <li>Try restarting the NFC service: toggle NFC off and back on in device settings</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="trouble-item">
                                <button class="trouble-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="trouble-4-body" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="trouble-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation"></i></span>
                                    <span>"Payment declined" error on NFC tap</span>
                                    <span class="trouble-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="trouble-body" id="trouble-4-body">
                                    <p>A declined payment may be due to:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Insufficient funds:</strong> The customer's wallet balance may be too low
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Transaction limit exceeded:</strong> Daily or per-transaction limits may have been reached
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Account restrictions:</strong> The customer's account may be locked or unverified
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Security hold:</strong> Unusual activity may have triggered a security review
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Contact <strong>support@mpaynetwork.com</strong> if the issue persists with error code
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="trouble-item">
                                <button class="trouble-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="trouble-5-body" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="trouble-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation"></i></span>
                                    <span>NFC works but is very slow</span>
                                    <span class="trouble-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="trouble-body" id="trouble-5-body">
                                    <p>Slow NFC transactions can be improved by:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Closing unnecessary background apps to free up device resources</li>
                                        <li>Ensuring a strong internet connection (switch to Wi-Fi if cellular is weak)</li>
                                        <li>Updating the MPay app to the latest version for performance improvements</li>
                                        <li>Clearing the MPay app cache: <strong>Settings → Apps → MPay → Clear Cache</strong>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Ensuring your device's NFC antenna area is clean and undamaged</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="callout danger">
                                <div class="callout-icon">
                                    <i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="callout-content">
                                    <strong>Still having issues?</strong>
                                    <p>If none of the above solutions work, visit our <a onclick="load_page('merchant_troubleshooting')" style="color:#dc2626;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:underline;">comprehensive troubleshooting guide</a> or contact support at <strong>support@mpaynetwork.com</strong> with your device model and error code.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <hr class="section-divider">
                        <!-- Section: FAQ -->
                        <section class="doc-section" id="mnfc_faq_accordion">
                            <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="faq-q-icon">Q</span>
                                    <span>Can I accept NFC payments without an internet connection?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer">
                                    <p>NFC payments require an active internet connection to verify the transaction in real-time. However, MPay supports an <strong>offline queue</strong> mode — if you briefly lose connection, the transaction is queued and processed automatically when connectivity is restored. Offline queue supports up to 5 pending transactions.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="faq-q-icon">Q</span>
                                    <span>What's the maximum distance for NFC tap-to-pay?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer">
                                    <p>NFC operates at a maximum range of <strong>4 cm (approximately 1.5 inches)</strong>. For the best experience, we recommend touching the devices back-to-back. The short range is a security feature that prevents unauthorized interception of payment data.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="faq-q-icon">Q</span>
                                    <span>Is NFC payment secure? Can someone intercept my transaction?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer">
                                    <p>Yes, NFC payments with MPay are extremely secure. All transactions are encrypted using <strong>AES-256 encryption</strong> and secured with <strong>tokenized payment data</strong>. The 4 cm range makes interception virtually impossible. Additionally, each transaction requires explicit confirmation from both the merchant and customer devices. No sensitive financial data is transmitted during the NFC handshake.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="faq-q-icon">Q</span>
                                    <span>Can customers pay with contactless bank cards via NFC?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer">
                                    <p>Currently, MPay NFC payments work between the <strong>MPay Merchant app</strong> and the <strong>MPay Consumer app</strong> (or Consumer's linked digital wallet). Direct contactless bank card acceptance (Visa/Mastercard contactless) is planned for a future release. Check our <a onclick="load_page('changelog_page')" style="color:#2563eb;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:underline;">changelog</a> for updates.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="faq-q-icon">Q</span>
                                    <span>Do I need a special reader or accessory for NFC payments?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer">
                                    <p>No! That's the beauty of MPay's NFC solution. Your <strong>smartphone is the payment terminal</strong>. No additional hardware, card readers, or accessories are needed. Just ensure your phone has built-in NFC capability and you're good to go.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="faq-item">
                                <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" role="button" tabindex="0">
                                    <span class="faq-q-icon">Q</span>
                                    <span>How fast is an NFC payment compared to QR code?</span>
                                    <span class="faq-chevron"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                                </button>
                                <div class="faq-answer">
                                    <p>NFC payments are typically <strong>faster than QR code payments</strong>. An NFC tap-to-pay transaction completes in <strong>1-3 seconds</strong>, while a QR code payment takes around <strong>5-8 seconds</strong> (including scanning time). NFC is ideal for high-volume, quick-service environments like cafes and transit.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
